    _s("Train Your Own AI Model - Complete Guide","YouTube Long","10min",
       "Everyone talks about using AI. Almost nobody talks about TRAINING your own. Today I'll show you how to create a custom AI model in under an hour.",
       "1. Why custom models\n2. Choosing a base model\n3. Preparing training data\n4. Training with LoRA\n5. Converting to GGUF\n6. Deploying to Ollama\n7. Testing and iterating",
       "Here's a secret the big AI companies don't want you to know: you can train your own custom AI model for free. Not fine-tune through an API - actually TRAIN a model that runs on your hardware, works offline, and does exactly what you need.\n\nWhy custom models? Generic AI gives generic answers. A custom model trained on YOUR data gives YOUR answers. We trained a model on our locksmith business data and it knows our exact pricing, service areas, response times, and speaks in our brand voice. No prompt engineering needed - it just knows.\n\nStep 1: Choose a base model. Gemma 2B is our go-to. It's small enough to train on consumer GPUs, fast enough for real-time use (1.3 second responses), and smart enough for most business tasks.\n\nStep 2: Prepare training data. Format: ChatML with system, user, and assistant messages. You need at least 30-50 high-quality examples. More is better - we used 71 for our sales model. The quality of your training data determines the quality of your model.\n\nStep 3: Train with LoRA. Low-Rank Adaptation lets you train efficiently. You're not retraining the whole model - just teaching it new behaviors. On an A100 GPU (rent one for $0.74/hour on Vast.ai), training takes 15-30 minutes for 50-100 examples.\n\nStep 4: Merge the LoRA weights back into the base model.\n\nStep 5: Convert to GGUF format and quantize to Q4_K_M. This shrinks the model from 5GB to 1.6GB with minimal quality loss.\n\nStep 6: Create an Ollama Modelfile and deploy. Now you can run your custom model with a single command: ollama run my-custom-model.\n\nStep 7: Test it. Run 50 different prompts and evaluate the responses. Fix any gaps by adding more training examples and retraining.\n\nWe trained 13 custom models in one night. Sales, coaching, phone answering, forex trading, coding, SEO - each one a specialist. A stack of 13 tiny models beats one giant model every time.",
       "Terminal recordings of full training pipeline. GPU monitoring during training. Before/after model responses. Ollama model running. Architecture diagram of LoRA training.",
       "Neural network visual with custom data flowing in. Text 'TRAIN YOUR OWN AI'. Laptop with terminal. Focused expression.",
       "train AI model,custom AI model,fine tune AI,LoRA training,train LLM,AI model training tutorial,Ollama custom model,GGUF conversion,train AI free,custom chatbot training,AI training data,machine learning tutorial,train AI on your data,AI training pipeline,Vast.ai training,GPU training,Gemma training,small AI model,hive dynamics,DIY AI model",
       "Complete guide to training your own custom AI model. From data preparation to deployment. Uses free tools (Ollama, LoRA) and costs under $1 in GPU rental.\n\nTraining script: https://hivecore.app/train\n#AITraining #CustomAI #MachineLearning #Tutorial",
       "Want us to train a custom model for your business? Visit hivecore.app. Subscribe for advanced AI training tutorials.",
       "YouTube Shorts,Blog"),

    _s("AI Will NOT Take Your Job (Here's Why)","YouTube Long","5min",
       "Everyone's scared AI is going to take their job. I'm going to tell you why that's wrong - and what you should ACTUALLY be worried about.",
       "1. The fear\n2. What AI actually replaces\n3. What AI can't do\n4. The real threat\n5. How to be irreplaceable",
       "Every week someone asks me: is AI going to take my job? Short answer: no. Longer answer: AI is not going to take your job. A person who knows how to use AI is going to take your job.\n\nHere's what AI actually replaces: repetitive tasks. Data entry. Basic writing. Simple customer inquiries. Schedule management. These aren't jobs - they're tasks within jobs. AI handles the boring parts so you can focus on the valuable parts.\n\nWhat AI absolutely cannot do in 2026: build genuine relationships. Show real empathy in complex situations. Make creative leaps. Navigate office politics. Negotiate face to face. Handle truly novel problems it's never seen before. Lead a team through a crisis.\n\nThe real threat isn't AI replacing you. It's you refusing to learn AI while your competitor embraces it. The locksmith who uses AI to answer calls at 3 AM gets the job. The one who sends it to voicemail doesn't. Same skills, same services - different outcome because one uses better tools.\n\nHow to be irreplaceable: become the person in your company who knows how to use AI. Be the one who sets up the automations, trains the models, interprets the AI output and makes it actionable. That person is not getting replaced. That person is getting promoted.\n\nEvery technology shift creates more jobs than it destroys. The internet was going to kill jobs. It created millions. Mobile was going to kill jobs. It created millions more. AI will do the same - but the jobs it creates require you to learn new skills.\n\nStart learning today. It's free. The resources are endless. And in 5 years, you'll either be glad you started now, or wish you had.",
       "Headlines about AI taking jobs. Counter-statistics about job creation. Examples of AI+human collaboration. Historical parallels (internet, mobile). Skills chart.",
       "Crossed-out robot with briefcase. Text 'AI WON'T TAKE YOUR JOB'. Confident expression. Red/blue split background.",
       "AI taking jobs,AI job loss,future of work AI,will AI replace me,AI job fears,AI and employment,AI career advice,AI skills,learn AI,AI future jobs,automation jobs,AI 2026 jobs,job security AI,AI proof career,upskill AI,AI and work,future proof career,AI workforce,hive dynamics,AI truth",
       "Stop panicking about AI taking your job. Here's what's REALLY happening and how to position yourself to benefit from the AI revolution instead of being left behind.\n\n#AI #FutureOfWork #CareerAdvice #AIJobs #2026",
       "Start learning AI today - free resources at hivecore.app. Subscribe for weekly career advice in the AI age.",
       "YouTube Shorts,TikTok,Instagram,Blog"),

