       "1. Case study 1: Locksmith\n2. Case study 2: Garage door company\n3. Case study 3: Paving contractor\n4. Common patterns\n5. Implementation steps",
       "Let me tell you about three real businesses that used AI to completely transform their revenue.\n\nBusiness 1: A locksmith in Destin, Florida. Before AI: missed 40% of calls after hours. Revenue: $8,000/month. After AI: AI phone agent catches every call 24/7. The 3 AM lockout calls that used to go to voicemail now get answered and dispatched instantly. After 4 months: revenue $22,000/month. That's a 175% increase from just answering the phone.\n\nBusiness 2: A garage door company in Fort Walton Beach. Before AI: spent $2,000/month on Google Ads with a 3% conversion rate. After AI: we built them an AI chatbot that engages every website visitor. We set up AI-generated content targeting long-tail keywords - 'garage door spring replacement cost Fort Walton Beach'. Organic traffic increased 340%. After 5 months: they cut ad spend to $500 and revenue went from $15,000 to $41,000.\n\nBusiness 3: A paving contractor in Pensacola. Before AI: relied entirely on word of mouth and yard signs. After AI: we gave them a complete digital presence - AI-optimized website, local SEO, Google Business Profile optimization, automated review requests after every job. They went from 2 leads per week to 14 leads per week. Revenue: $12,000/month to $38,000/month.\n\nThe common patterns across all three: Answer every inquiry instantly (AI phone + chatbot). Create content that targets local search terms. Automate follow-up so no lead goes cold. Ask for reviews automatically.\n\nImplementation steps: Step 1 - set up AI phone answering (1 day). Step 2 - deploy chatbot on website (1 hour). Step 3 - start content generation targeting local keywords (ongoing). Step 4 - automate review requests (2 hours). Step 5 - optimize Google Business Profile (1 hour).\n\nTotal time investment: 2 days. Revenue impact: 2-3x within 6 months. Every one of these tools is available right now at hivecore.app.",
       "Revenue charts before/after for each business. Maps showing service areas. Phone call recordings (with permission). Website traffic analytics. Google search rankings.",
