    _s("How to Build a Service Business Empire","YouTube Long","10min",
       "One truck. One person. One city. That's how every service empire starts. I'll show you how to go from one to fifty cities using AI.",
       "1. The one-city model\n2. Systematize everything\n3. AI as your force multiplier\n4. Multi-city expansion\n5. Hiring and training\n6. Revenue stacking",
       "Every service business empire started the same way. One person. One truck. One city. But the ones that stayed small did everything manually. The ones that became empires built systems. Here's how to build yours.\n\nThe one-city model: Master one city first. Learn every neighborhood, every competitor, every customer pattern. In Destin, we know that lockout calls spike on Friday and Saturday nights near the harbor. We know garage door calls peak in hurricane season. This local knowledge is your competitive advantage.\n\nSystematize everything: If you're doing it manually, it can be automated. Phone answering - AI. Scheduling - automated calendar. Dispatch - AI routing. Follow-up - automated email sequences. Reviews - automated text requests. Content - AI generation. When every process is a system, it can be replicated.\n\nAI as force multiplier: One person with AI can serve as many customers as a 10-person team without AI. Our phone agent handles unlimited simultaneous calls. Our chatbot serves unlimited website visitors. Our content engine produces unlimited pages. You are one person with the capabilities of ten.\n\nMulti-city expansion: Once your systems work in one city, replicate. We went from Destin to 50 cities by duplicating our template. Each city gets a customized website, localized content, local phone number, and targeted SEO. The AI handles everything - you just add cities.\n\nHiring: When you expand, hire technicians first, not office staff. AI handles the office. You need boots on the ground doing the actual work. Train each tech using AI-generated training materials customized to their skill level.\n\nRevenue stacking: Don't just offer one service. A locksmith can add key duplication, safe installation, security audits, smart lock installation, access control systems, garage door service. Each service multiplies revenue per customer.\n\nStart with one city. Systematize. Expand. Repeat until you're in every city in your state. That's how empires are built.",
       "Map showing expansion from one city to fifty. System diagrams. Revenue growth charts. Organizational structure evolution. Before/after of one-person vs empire operation.",
       "One truck growing into a fleet. Map expanding outward. Text 'BUILD AN EMPIRE'. Determined, visionary expression.",
       "service business empire,scale service business,grow service business,multi city business,expand business,AI scaling,service business growth,locksmith empire,contractor scaling,franchise alternative,build business empire,expand to new cities,grow with AI,service area expansion,multi location business,scale with systems,business systems,service company growth,hive dynamics,build empire",
       "How to go from 1 truck in 1 city to a 50-city service empire. The AI-powered expansion playbook for any service business.\n\nhivecore.app\n#BusinessEmpire #Scaling #ServiceBusiness #Growth #AIScaling",
       "Ready to expand? Start with the free city-expansion toolkit at hivecore.app. Subscribe for the empire-building series.",
       "YouTube Shorts,Blog"),

    _s("Facebook Ads for Local Business - $5 a Day","YouTube Long","10min",
       "Five dollars a day. That's all you need for Facebook Ads that actually bring in local customers. I'll set up a campaign with you live.",
       "1. Setting up Business Manager\n2. Audience targeting for local\n3. Ad creative with AI\n4. Budget strategy\n5. Optimization tips\n6. Common mistakes\n7. Expected results",
       "Five dollars a day. One hundred fifty dollars a month. That's what it costs to run Facebook Ads that consistently bring in local customers. Let me set up a campaign with you right now.\n\nStep 1: Go to business.facebook.com. Create a Business Manager account. Create an ad account. Install the Facebook Pixel on your website. This takes 10 minutes.\n\nStep 2: Audience targeting. This is where local businesses win. Target your city with a 15-25 mile radius. Age 25-65. Homeowners. That's it. Don't over-target. Facebook's algorithm is smart enough to find the right people within that audience.\n\nStep 3: Ad creative. Use AI to generate ad copy. Prompt: 'Write 5 Facebook ad variations for a locksmith business in Destin FL. Include a specific offer, urgency element, and clear call to action. Keep each under 90 words.' Then use AI image generation for the visual - a professional locksmith image with your branding.\n\nBest performing ad format for local businesses: 'Locked out in [City]? We're 20 minutes away. 24/7 emergency locksmith service. Call now: [number]. $15 off for first-time customers.' Simple, clear, actionable.\n\nStep 4: Budget. Set $5/day. Choose 'Leads' as your campaign objective. Let Facebook optimize delivery. Don't touch the campaign for 3-5 days - the algorithm needs time to learn.\n\nStep 5: Optimization. After 5 days, check which ad variation performs best. Kill the losers. Double the budget on winners. Test new variations weekly.\n\nCommon mistakes: Targeting too broad or too narrow. Changing the campaign every day. Not having a landing page that matches the ad. Not following up on leads fast enough - leads go cold in 5 minutes.\n\nExpected results at $5/day: 500-1,500 people see your ad daily. 5-15 clicks per day. 1-3 leads per day. At a $150 average job value, even 1 lead per day = $4,500/month from a $150 ad spend. That's a 30x return.",
       "Live screen recording of campaign setup. Ad creative examples. Targeting selection walkthrough. Results dashboard after running. ROI calculator.",
       "Facebook logo with $5 bill. Text '$5/DAY ADS'. Results graph showing ROI. Hands-on tutorial vibe.",
       "Facebook ads local business,Facebook ads $5,local Facebook ads,Facebook ads tutorial,Facebook ads small business,Facebook ads 2026,cheap Facebook ads,Facebook ads ROI,local business ads,Facebook leads,Facebook advertising,Facebook ad targeting,local ad strategy,Facebook business manager,Facebook ads locksmith,Facebook ads contractor,small budget ads,Facebook marketing,hive dynamics,Facebook ads guide",
       "Complete Facebook Ads tutorial for local businesses on a $5/day budget. Live setup, targeting, AI creative, and optimization. 30x ROI is realistic.\n\nhivecore.app\n#FacebookAds #LocalMarketing #SmallBusiness #DigitalMarketing",
       "Start your $5/day campaign today. Subscribe for the weekly ad optimization series.",
       "YouTube Shorts,Blog"),

    _s("How I Built 63 Websites for ONE Company","YouTube Long","10min",
       "Sixty-three professional websites. One afternoon. One Python script. Zero web designers. Here's exactly how and why.",
       "1. Why 63 websites\n2. The website generator\n3. AI content per site\n4. SEO at scale\n5. Results and traffic\n6. Managing them all",
       "I built 63 professional websites in one afternoon. Not landing pages. Full websites with 12 sections, 1,900+ words each, unique content, local SEO, AI chatbots, and contact forms. Here's why and how.\n\nWhy 63? We serve 50+ cities across the Florida panhandle. Each city needs its own website optimized for local search. 'Locksmith Destin FL' and 'Locksmith Pensacola FL' are completely different searches with different competitors. One website can't rank for both.\n\nThe generator: A Python script that takes a city name, service type, and business details, then generates a complete HTML website. It uses AI to create unique content for each city - not templates with the city name swapped in, but genuinely unique content that mentions local landmarks, neighborhoods, and community details.\n\nEach site includes: Hero section with local imagery. Services list with descriptions. Pricing guide. FAQ section with 10 city-specific questions. Service area map. About section. Contact form. AI chatbot widget. Google Maps embed. Schema markup. Social media links. Review section.\n\nContent: AI generates approximately 1,900 words per site. Each one is unique. The Destin site mentions the Harbor, Henderson Beach, and the Emerald Coast. The Pensacola site mentions Palafox Street, the naval base, and the historic district. Google sees these as completely different, valuable pages.\n\nSEO: Each site has unique title tags, meta descriptions, alt text, and heading structure. All optimized for their specific city + service keyword combination.\n\nResults after 2 months: 42 of the 63 sites appear on Google. 18 are on the first page for their target keywords. Combined organic traffic: 2,400 visits per month. All from a single afternoon of work.\n\nManagement: One Cloudflare tunnel routes all 63 domains to our server. One Python process serves all sites. Updates propagate to all 63 simultaneously.\n\nThis is what AI-powered scale looks like. One person, one afternoon, 63 professional websites.",
       "Code editor showing generator script. Side-by-side comparison of different city sites. SEO ranking screenshots. Traffic analytics. Architecture diagram of hosting setup.",
       "Grid of 63 website screenshots. Text '63 WEBSITES, 1 AFTERNOON'. Python logo. Amazed expression.",
       "build multiple websites,website generator,AI website builder,63 websites,bulk website creation,Python website generator,local SEO websites,city-specific websites,website automation,mass website deployment,AI web development,auto generate website,website at scale,SEO website builder,local business websites,locksmith websites,service area websites,website factory,hive dynamics,programmatic SEO",
       "63 professional websites built in one afternoon using Python and AI. Each with unique content, local SEO, and AI chatbots. Here's the complete system.\n\nhivecore.app\n#WebDev #AI #Automation #SEO #ScaleUp",
       "Want the website generator code? Link in the description. Subscribe for more AI-powered scaling strategies.",
       "YouTube Shorts,TikTok,Blog"),

    _s("How to Hire Your First Employee","YouTube Long","5min",
       "Hiring wrong costs $15,000 on average. Here's how to hire right the first time using AI to screen, test, and onboard.",
       "1. When to hire\n2. Writing the job post with AI\n3. AI screening\n4. Interview framework\n5. Trial period\n6. Onboarding with AI",
       "The average bad hire costs $15,000 in lost productivity, training, and rehiring. Your first hire is the most important one. Here's how to get it right.\n\nWhen to hire: When you're consistently turning away work. Not when you're busy once. Not when you hope to grow. When you have more work than you can handle for 3+ consecutive months. For us, that was when AI was booking more appointments than we could service.\n\nJob post: Use AI to write it, but make it human. 'We don't want a resume. We want to know: Have you ever fixed something at 2 AM because someone was counting on you? That's what we do.' Real job posts attract real people.\n\nAI screening: For 100 applications, use AI to rank them based on your criteria. Relevant experience, location, availability, culture fit signals in their application. Narrows 100 to 10 in minutes instead of hours.\n\nInterview framework: Three questions that matter. 1: Tell me about a time you solved a problem nobody asked you to solve. 2: What would you do if a customer was angry about a price after the job was done? 3: What's the most interesting thing you've learned in the last month? These reveal problem-solving ability, customer handling, and growth mindset.\n\nTrial period: One week paid trial. Real work, real customers, real pressure. This tells you more than any interview. At the end of the week, ask your customers what they thought. Their feedback is the only performance review that matters.\n\nOnboarding with AI: Create AI-generated training materials specific to your business. Standard procedures, pricing guides, customer scripts, troubleshooting guides. The new hire studies these and can reference them anytime. Our AI chatbot even serves as a 24/7 training assistant - new hires can ask it questions about procedures.",
       "Job posting examples. Screening dashboard. Interview recording setup. Training material examples. Onboarding checklist.",
       "Two people shaking hands with AI checkmark. Text 'HIRE RIGHT'. Clipboard and checklist visual. Professional mentoring pose.",
       "how to hire,first employee,hiring tips,small business hiring,hiring with AI,AI screening,job posting tips,interview questions,onboarding,hiring process,first hire,when to hire,hiring mistakes,employee onboarding,AI recruitment,hiring framework,small business team,grow team,hive dynamics,hiring guide",
       "How to hire your first employee without making a $15K mistake. AI-powered screening, proven interview questions, and smart onboarding.\n\nhivecore.app\n#Hiring #SmallBusiness #FirstEmployee #BusinessGrowth",
       "Download the hiring checklist at hivecore.app/hiring. Subscribe for team-building strategies.",
       "Blog"),

    _s("Revenue Streams - How We Make Money 7 Ways","YouTube Long","10min",
       "One income stream is a job. Multiple income streams is a business. Here are our 7 revenue streams and how to build your own.",
       "1. Service fees\n2. Platform subscriptions\n3. AI model training\n4. Content services\n5. Lead generation\n6. Consulting\n7. Forex trading\n8. How to add revenue streams",
       "If your business has one revenue stream, you don't have a business. You have a job with extra steps. Here are 7 ways we make money simultaneously.\n\nStream 1: Service fees. The bread and butter. Locksmith services, garage door repairs, paving jobs. Direct service for direct payment. This is where most businesses stop. Don't stop here.\n\nStream 2: Platform subscriptions. Our AI platform at hivecore.app. $29.99/month basic, up to $2,997/month enterprise. Recurring revenue that grows every month as we add customers. This is the most valuable stream because it's predictable.\n\nStream 3: AI model training. We train custom AI models for other businesses. $5,000-15,000 per model. A restaurant chain needs an AI that knows their menu and policies. A law firm needs an AI that handles intake calls. We train it on their data and deploy it.\n\nStream 4: Content services. AI-generated content packages for businesses. 30 blog posts, 60 social media posts, 4 email campaigns per month. $500-2,000/month per client.\n\nStream 5: Lead generation. We generate leads through our 63 websites and sell them to service providers. $30-100 per qualified lead. The websites generate traffic, AI qualifies the leads, we connect them to the right provider.\n\nStream 6: Consulting. AI implementation consulting for mid-size businesses. $5,000-20,000 per engagement. Walk in, audit their processes, implement AI solutions, train their team.\n\nStream 7: Forex trading. Our AI trading bot runs USD/JPY positions. It's not our biggest stream, but it's completely passive. The bot trades 24/5 with no human input.\n\nHow to add streams: Start with one that complements what you already do. If you're a locksmith, add smart lock installation (new skill, same customer). Then add a monthly monitoring subscription. Then add training for other locksmiths. Each stream builds on the last.\n\nSeven streams means if one has a bad month, six others keep you profitable. That's not just income - that's stability.",
       "Revenue pie chart showing all 7 streams. Individual stream deep-dives with numbers. Growth chart of combined revenue. Comparison: 1 stream vs 7 streams.",
       "Seven pillars with money flowing from each. Text '7 REVENUE STREAMS'. Dollar signs and business icons. Confident business presentation.",
       "multiple revenue streams,income streams,diversify income,how to make money,business revenue,seven income streams,passive income,service business revenue,subscription revenue,AI revenue,consulting income,lead gen revenue,forex trading income,add revenue streams,business model,income diversification,multiple income,revenue strategy,hive dynamics,money streams",
       "One income stream is a job. Seven is an empire. Here's exactly how we built 7 simultaneous revenue streams and how you can add yours.\n\nhivecore.app\n#RevenueStreams #Income #Business #Entrepreneur #PassiveIncome",
       "Pick one new revenue stream to add this month. Subscribe for the deep-dive series on each stream.",
       "YouTube Shorts,TikTok,Blog"),
