       "In 10 minutes you'll write your first Python program. No experience needed. I learned Python to build a multi-million dollar AI system and I started exactly where you are.",
       "1. Install Python\n2. Your first program\n3. Variables and types\n4. If statements\n5. Loops\n6. Functions\n7. Build something real",
       "Python is the most in-demand programming language in the world. It powers AI, automation, web development, data science, and pretty much everything else. And you're going to learn it in 10 minutes.\n\nMinute 1: Install Python. Go to python.org, click Download, install it. Check 'Add to PATH.' Open your terminal, type 'python3', and you're in.\n\nMinute 2: Your first program. Type: print('Hello World'). Press enter. Congratulations, you just wrote Python. Every programmer in history started here.\n\nMinute 3-4: Variables. Think of variables as labeled boxes. name = 'Chris'. age = 30. price = 29.99. Python figures out the type automatically. Strings for text, integers for whole numbers, floats for decimals.\n\nMinute 5-6: If statements. Making decisions: if age >= 18: print('You can vote'). else: print('Too young'). Indentation matters in Python. The colon and indent is how Python knows what's inside the if block.\n\nMinute 7-8: Loops. Doing things repeatedly: for i in range(5): print(f'Attempt {i}'). This runs 5 times. While loops: while count < 10: count += 1. Loops are how you process data, send emails, check conditions.\n\nMinute 9: Functions. Reusable blocks of code: def calculate_price(base, quantity): return base * quantity * 0.9. Now call it: total = calculate_price(29.99, 3). Functions let you write code once and use it everywhere.\n\nMinute 10: Build something real. Let's combine everything into a price calculator: get user input, validate it, calculate total with discount, display result. That's a real, useful program in 10 lines of Python.\n\nWhat's next? You know enough to start building real tools. Our entire Hive system - 139 services, 63 websites, AI phone agents - is all Python. Everything you see us build, you can build too. Start with the exercises in the pinned comment.",
