       "Forget the fake gurus. Here are 5 AI passive income streams that actually work because I'm running all 5 right now.",
       "1. AI content licensing\n2. AI phone answering SaaS\n3. Automated lead gen\n4. AI-powered websites\n5. AI trading\n6. Monthly income breakdown",
       "Every passive income video on YouTube is selling you a dream. I'm going to show you 5 passive income streams I actually run, with real numbers.\n\nStream 1: AI content licensing. We generate content using AI and license it to businesses. Blog posts, social media content, email campaigns. Set up the pipeline once, it generates content daily. We charge $500/month per client for automated content delivery. 5 clients = $2,500/month. Time investment: 2 hours/week monitoring quality.\n\nStream 2: AI phone answering SaaS. Our AI answers calls for businesses 24/7. They pay $29.99-$299/month. The AI runs on our servers. Marginal cost per new customer: near zero. Once built, it scales infinitely. Current run rate builds with each new subscriber.\n\nStream 3: Automated lead generation. Our 63 websites generate organic traffic and capture leads automatically. We sell leads to service providers at $30-100 each. The websites run themselves. SEO keeps improving. Leads flow in daily.\n\nStream 4: AI-powered websites. We build and host websites for businesses. $19.99/month per site. Built once with AI, hosted on our infrastructure. Cost per site: pennies. Maintenance: automated. Updates: AI-generated.\n\nStream 5: AI forex trading. Our bot trades 24/5. No manual intervention. Small, consistent gains compound. Not life-changing income on its own, but truly passive - it runs whether I'm awake or not.\n\nMonthly breakdown: Content licensing: $2,500. Phone answering: growing. Lead gen: variable. Websites: growing with each client. Forex: variable.\n\nThe key insight: none of these required zero effort. They all took significant upfront work to build. But now they run with minimal maintenance. That's real passive income - frontload the work, harvest the results.\n\nPassive doesn't mean effortless. It means the income isn't proportional to your time. You build the system once, it produces forever.",
