SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-locksmith"].extend([
    _s("Emergency Lockout - What to Expect","YouTube Long","5min","Locked out? Here is exactly what happens when you call us, what it costs, and how long it takes.","1. The call\n2. Dispatch\n3. Arrival\n4. The opening\n5. Cost and payment","You call us. Our AI answers in 2 seconds, gets your location, confirms it is a lockout, and dispatches the nearest technician. ETA: 15-25 minutes in our service area. The tech arrives in a branded vehicle with ID. They assess the lock type. 95% of residential lockouts are opened non-destructively in 5-15 minutes using professional tools. No drilling unless absolutely necessary. Cost: $45-85 for standard residential. $85-150 for high-security or unusual locks. We accept all payment methods and provide a written receipt with warranty. Total time from call to inside your home: typically under 30 minutes.","Real lockout service footage.","Locksmith arriving at door. Timeline graphic.","emergency lockout,locksmith service,lockout cost,locksmith what to expect,call a locksmith","What to expect from an emergency lockout service. Timeline, cost, and process.\n#Locksmith #Emergency #Lockout","Save this for emergencies. Subscribe.","YouTube Shorts,TikTok"),
    _s("Commercial vs Residential Locksmith","YouTube Long","5min","The same lock on a house costs $50 to fix. On a business? $200. Here is why.","1. Different hardware\n2. Different regulations\n3. Different skills\n4. Pricing differences","Commercial locks are built differently. Grade 1 commercial hardware vs Grade 3 residential. ADA compliance required on commercial doors. Master key systems for building management. Access control with key cards and codes. Fire code requirements for emergency exits. Insurance requirements are higher. The skill set is more specialized. That is why commercial locksmith work commands higher prices. But the margins are better and the contracts are recurring. If you are a locksmith, get commercial certified.","Commercial vs residential lock comparison.","Two doors - home and office.","commercial locksmith,residential locksmith,locksmith comparison,commercial locks","Commercial vs residential locksmith explained.\n#Locksmith #Commercial #Business","Need commercial service? hivecore.app.","YouTube Shorts,Blog"),
    _s("Key Duplication - Everything You Need to Know","YouTube Long","5min","A key copy costs $3. A restricted key copy costs $75. Here is why and how to know which you have.","1. Standard keys\n2. Restricted keys\n3. High-security keys\n4. Where to get copies\n5. Smart alternatives","Standard brass keys: $2-5 at any hardware store. Takes 60 seconds. Restricted keys (Medeco, Mul-T-Lock): $25-75, only through authorized dealers. Must show ID and authorization card. High-security keys have unique patterns that prevent unauthorized copying. How to tell: if your key has DO NOT DUPLICATE stamped on it, it is restricted (though legally that stamp is not enforceable for standard keys). For maximum security, use a key system that requires a security card for duplication. Smart alternative: keypad or smart locks eliminate key duplication concerns entirely.","Key types comparison. Duplication process.","Different keys with price tags.","key duplication,copy keys,key cutting,restricted keys,high security keys","Key duplication guide. From $3 brass to $75 high-security.\n#Keys #Locksmith #Security","Need keys? Visit hivecore.app. Subscribe.","YouTube Shorts,Blog"),
    _s("High Security Locks - Are They Worth It?","YouTube Long","5min","A standard deadbolt costs $25. A high-security lock costs $250. Is it worth 10x the price?","1. What makes them high-security\n2. Pick resistance\n3. Drill resistance\n4. Key control\n5. Who needs them","High-security locks have: pick-resistant pin configurations (spool pins, serrated pins, mushroom pins), drill-resistant hardened steel inserts, restricted key blanks preventing unauthorized copies, reinforced housings, and UL 437 certification. Are they worth it? For most residential homes: probably not. A standard Grade 1 deadbolt plus a reinforced strike plate provides excellent security for $50-75. For businesses, high-value homes, or anyone with a specific threat: absolutely worth the investment. The key control alone (knowing exactly who has copies) is invaluable for commercial properties.","Lock comparison. Pick attempt on each type.","Standard vs high-security lock.","high security locks,Medeco,Mul-T-Lock,lock security,best locks","High-security locks: when $250 is worth it.\n#Security #Locks #Locksmith","Free security assessment at hivecore.app.","YouTube Shorts,Blog"),
    _s("Locksmith Business Marketing - What Works","YouTube Long","10min","I have tested every marketing channel for a locksmith business. Here is what actually generates calls.","1. Google Business Profile (#1)\n2. SEO content (#2)\n3. AI phone answering (#3)\n4. Review management (#4)\n5. What does NOT work","Number 1 by far: Google Business Profile. Free listing, appears in Maps, generates the most calls. Optimize it fully. Number 2: SEO content targeting local keywords. Emergency locksmith [city]. 24 hour lockout [city]. Takes 2-3 months but free traffic forever. Number 3: AI phone answering. Captures every call including after-hours, which is 30-40% of all calls. Number 4: Review management. After every job, automated text asking for a Google review. More reviews = higher ranking = more calls. What does NOT work: Facebook ads (low intent), Yelp (pay to play), door hangers (low conversion), Yellow Pages (dead). Focus on Google. Everything else is secondary.","Marketing channel comparison. ROI per channel.","Marketing funnel for locksmiths.","locksmith marketing,locksmith SEO,locksmith Google,locksmith business growth,marketing for locksmiths","Locksmith marketing: what actually generates calls.\n#Locksmith #Marketing #SmallBusiness","Marketing toolkit at hivecore.app. Subscribe.","YouTube Shorts,Blog")
])

SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-home"].extend([
    _s("How We Use AI to Dispatch Home Service Techs","YouTube Long","5min","When you call for a locksmith, AI decides who comes to your door. Here is how.","1. Call comes in\n2. AI answers\n3. Job creation\n4. Tech assignment\n5. Customer notification","Customer calls. AI answers in 2 seconds. Gets their location, identifies the problem, provides a price estimate. AI creates a job in our dispatch system. Then the magic: AI checks all available technicians. Considers proximity (who is closest), skill match (residential vs commercial), current workload, and schedule. Assigns the optimal tech. Sends them job details via text. Tells the customer: your tech John will be there in approximately 18 minutes. All in under 10 seconds. No dispatcher needed. The tech shows up, does the work, AI sends a review request. Fully automated from call to completion.","Dispatch system in action.","Map with AI routing.","AI dispatch,home service dispatch,automated dispatch,tech routing","How AI dispatches our technicians.\n#AI #HomeService #Dispatch","Want AI dispatch? hivecore.app.","YouTube Shorts,Blog"),
    _s("Home Security Tips That Actually Work","YouTube Long","5min","Most home security advice is useless. Here are the 5 things that actually prevent break-ins.","1. Reinforce entry points\n2. Lighting\n3. Visibility\n4. Routine variation\n5. Neighbor network","Number 1: Reinforce entry points. 3-inch screws in strike plates and hinges. This alone stops most kick-ins. $10 and 20 minutes. Number 2: Motion-activated exterior lighting on all entry points. Burglars hate light. Number 3: Trim bushes near windows and doors. Remove hiding spots. Number 4: Vary your routine. Use smart light timers when away. Do not post vacations on social media. Number 5: Know your neighbors. The best security system is a neighbor who notices a strange van in your driveway. These five things cost under $100 total and are more effective than any alarm system.","Security upgrades demonstrated.","House with security checkpoints.","home security tips,prevent break in,home safety,security advice","5 home security tips that actually work.\n#HomeSecurity #Safety #Tips","Free security checklist at hivecore.app.","YouTube Shorts,TikTok,Instagram")
])

SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-creative"].extend([
    _s("AI Voice Over - Professional Quality for Free","YouTube Long","5min","Professional voiceover used to cost $100-500 per minute. AI does it for free. Here is how.","1. ElevenLabs\n2. Voice cloning\n3. Multi-language\n4. Business use cases\n5. Quality comparison","ElevenLabs free tier: enough characters for several video voiceovers per month. Upload 30 seconds of your voice, get a clone that speaks any text in your voice. Multi-language: generate voiceovers in 29 languages from one voice sample. Business uses: video narration, phone system greetings, training materials, podcast intros. Quality: neural voices are nearly indistinguishable from human recordings. We use AI voice for all our phone system greetings and video narration. Cost: $0. Previous cost with voice actors: $300-500 per project.","Voice generation demo. Quality comparison.","Microphone with AI waveform.","AI voice over,AI narration,ElevenLabs,free voice over,AI audio","Professional voiceover with AI. Free.\n#AIVoice #VoiceOver #FreeTools","Try ElevenLabs today. Subscribe.","YouTube Shorts,TikTok"),
    _s("How AI is Changing Creative Work","YouTube Long","10min","AI is not replacing creatives. It is giving them superpowers. Here is what the creative industry looks like in 2026.","1. Writing\n2. Visual art\n3. Music\n4. Video\n5. The new creative","Writing: AI handles first drafts, research, and formatting. Writers focus on voice, perspective, and storytelling. Productivity: 5x. Visual art: AI generates concepts and variations. Artists refine, curate, and add human touch. Speed: 10x. Music: AI generates backgrounds, beats, and variations. Musicians compose, perform, and produce. Output: 3x. Video: AI handles scripts, voiceovers, thumbnails, and editing assistance. Creators focus on personality, connection, and storytelling. Production speed: 4x. The new creative is not someone who can draw or write. It is someone who can direct AI and add the human elements that make content resonate. The barrier to entry is lower than ever. The ceiling is higher than ever.","Creative industry examples.","Artist with AI tools surrounding them.","AI creative,AI art,AI music,AI writing,creative AI,future of creative work","How AI is transforming every creative field.\n#AICreative #FutureOfWork #Art","Subscribe for creative AI content.","YouTube Shorts,Blog"),
    _s("Build a Creative Portfolio with AI Tools","YouTube Long","5min","No design skills needed. Build a professional creative portfolio in one afternoon with AI.","1. Logo\n2. Website\n3. Sample work\n4. Case studies\n5. Social proof","Step 1: AI-generated logo (Ideogram or Midjourney). Step 2: Portfolio website (AI generates the code and design). Step 3: Create sample work using AI tools - show what you can create for clients. Blog post examples, social media graphics, email campaigns, video scripts. Step 4: Write case studies showing the process and results. AI helps write compelling narratives around your work. Step 5: Create testimonial templates. As you get real clients, fill them in. Launch your portfolio in one afternoon. Total cost: $0. When a potential client asks for your portfolio, send them a professional URL instead of a blank stare.","Portfolio creation process.","Portfolio website screenshot.","creative portfolio,AI portfolio,build portfolio,freelance portfolio","Build a creative portfolio with AI in one afternoon.\n#Portfolio #Creative #Freelance","Start building today. Subscribe.","YouTube Shorts,Blog")
])

SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-podcast"].extend([
    _s("AI Ethics and Regulation - Where Do We Draw the Line?","Podcast","30min","AI can clone voices, generate deepfakes, and make autonomous decisions. Where should we draw the ethical line?","1. Voice cloning ethics\n2. Content generation\n3. Autonomous decisions\n4. Regulation approaches\n5. Industry self-regulation","Voice cloning: incredible technology, terrifying potential for misuse. Our position: always disclose AI-generated audio. Never clone without consent. Content generation: AI can write articles, create images, generate videos. Should all AI content be labeled? Probably yes. Should it be banned? Absolutely not. Autonomous decisions: AI trading bots make financial decisions. AI dispatch assigns workers. AI phone agents book appointments. Where does AI authority end and human judgment begin? Regulation: EU AI Act is the most comprehensive. US is lagging. The challenge: regulate too little and harm occurs. Regulate too much and innovation dies. Our approach: transparent about AI use, ethical in implementation, and supportive of sensible regulation that protects people without killing innovation.","Ethics debate format. Regulation comparison charts.","Scales of justice with AI.","AI ethics,AI regulation,deepfake ethics,AI morality,AI policy","AI ethics and regulation. Where do we draw the line?\n#AIEthics #Regulation #Podcast","Subscribe for the ethics series.","YouTube Long,Blog"),
    _s("Mac Cluster vs Cloud GPUs - The Inference Battle","Podcast","30min","We are planning a Mac Mini cluster for AI inference. Is it better than renting cloud GPUs?","1. Mac Mini M2 specs\n2. Cloud GPU costs\n3. Performance comparison\n4. Power consumption\n5. Total cost of ownership","Mac Mini M2 24GB: $1,100 used. Unified memory means full 24GB available for AI models. Two of them: 48GB pooled with exo for distributed inference. Runs 24/7 silently. Power: 15 watts. Monthly electricity: $3. Cloud equivalent: A100 80GB at $0.74/hour = $530/month. 3 months of cloud = cost of 1 Mac Mini that runs forever. Performance: Mac M2 runs inference on 7B-13B models at 20-40 tokens/second. Good enough for phone answering at 1.3 second response time. Cloud wins on raw performance but loses on economics for always-on inference. Our plan: train on NVIDIA GPUs (rent by the hour), deploy on Apple Silicon (own forever). Best of both worlds.","Hardware comparison charts. Cost analysis over time.","Mac Mini vs cloud GPU.","Mac cluster,Apple Silicon AI,cloud GPU comparison,inference cost,Mac Mini AI","Mac cluster vs cloud GPUs for AI inference.\n#MacMini #AppleSilicon #AI #Podcast","Subscribe for hardware analysis.","YouTube Long,Blog"),
    _s("Building a Tech Company Without Venture Capital","Podcast","30min","98% of startups that raise VC fail. 100% of bootstrapped businesses that find customers survive. Here is the case for bootstrapping.","1. VC vs bootstrap\n2. Ownership\n3. Speed vs sustainability\n4. When VC makes sense\n5. The bootstrap playbook","VC sounds glamorous. Someone gives you $2 million. But they take 20-30% of your company. They put you on a board. They want 10x returns in 5 years. The pressure leads to spending before earning. Bootstrapping: you own 100%. Every decision is yours. You grow at the speed of revenue, not burn rate. Is it slower? Yes. Is it more sustainable? Dramatically. When does VC make sense? Capital-intensive hardware. Winner-take-all markets. Network effects that require massive scale fast. For a service business with AI? Bootstrap. Your costs are near zero. Your margins are high. Your customer acquisition can be organic. The bootstrap playbook: charge from day one. Keep costs near zero. Grow through revenue not investment. Own everything.","Comparison statistics. Success rate data.","VC money vs bootstrap growth.","bootstrap startup,no VC,bootstrapped business,indie startup,self funded","Building a tech company without VC. The case for bootstrapping.\n#Bootstrap #Startup #NoVC #Podcast","Subscribe for founder strategy content.","YouTube Long,Blog")
])


