SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-ai"].extend([
    _s("AI Agents That Book Appointments While You Sleep","YouTube","14:00","What if your phone never stopped answering — even at 3AM?","1. The problem with missed calls\n2. How AI phone agents work\n3. Building one from scratch\n4. Real results from our system\n5. Cost breakdown vs hiring","Every missed call is a missed sale. Studies show 80 percent of callers who reach voicemail never call back. But what if you had an AI agent answering 24/7? Today I will show you exactly how we built an AI phone system that books appointments automatically. We use open-source models fine-tuned on real call data. The setup costs less than one employee lunch per day. Let me walk you through the architecture step by step.","Phone ringing animation, call flow diagrams, dashboard screenshots, code editor with Python","Split screen: sleeping person on left, AI agent handling calls on right, green dollar signs floating up","ai phone agent,automated booking,ai receptionist,missed calls,appointment scheduling,twilio ai,voice ai,phone automation,ai answering service,small business ai,24/7 answering,ai assistant,phone bot,call handling,virtual receptionist,ai customer service,automated calls,business automation,ai tools,phone system","Learn how to build an AI phone agent that answers calls and books appointments 24/7 using open-source models and Twilio.","Download our free AI phone agent blueprint in the description!","TikTok, Instagram Reels, LinkedIn"),
    _s("The 5 AI Tools That Actually Make Money in 2026","YouTube","12:00","Forget ChatGPT wrappers. These tools generate real revenue.","1. AI phone agents for service businesses\n2. Content repurposing engines\n3. Lead scoring and qualification\n4. Automated SEO content\n5. Custom fine-tuned models as a service","Everyone talks about AI tools but nobody talks about which ones actually make money. I have tested over 200 AI products this year and narrowed it down to five that consistently generate revenue. Number one is AI phone agents. Service businesses lose thousands in missed calls. An AI agent that answers and books appointments pays for itself day one. Number two is content repurposing. One video becomes seven pieces of content automatically. Let me show you each tool and exactly how much they earn.","Tool dashboards, revenue screenshots, comparison charts, live demos of each tool","Gold bars stacked with AI circuit patterns, text overlay: 5 AI Tools That Actually Pay, money green accent","ai tools 2026,make money with ai,ai business tools,ai revenue,ai phone agent,content repurposing,lead scoring,seo ai,fine tuned models,ai saas,ai side hustle,profitable ai,ai automation,money making ai,ai business ideas,ai tools that work,best ai tools,ai entrepreneur,ai income,passive income ai","Discover the 5 AI tools that are actually generating revenue in 2026 — not hype, real money.","Grab our AI revenue toolkit — link in description!","TikTok, Instagram Reels, Blog Post"),
    _s("How We Fine-Tuned 13 AI Models on a Single GPU","YouTube","18:00","You do not need a data center. You need a strategy.","1. Why small specialized models beat large general ones\n2. Our stacked mini-model architecture\n3. Training pipeline on consumer hardware\n4. LoRA and quantization explained simply\n5. Results and benchmarks","Big tech wants you to think you need millions of dollars to train AI. That is a lie. We fine-tuned 13 specialized models on a single consumer GPU and they outperform GPT-4 on their specific tasks. The secret is specialization. Instead of one giant model that does everything okay, we train tiny models that do one thing brilliantly. A sales model. A coding model. A phone answering model. Each one is 1.6 gigabytes. Each one cold-starts in two seconds. Let me show you exactly how.","GPU close-ups, training loss curves, terminal output, model comparison charts, architecture diagrams","13 small model icons arranged in a honeycomb pattern around a single GPU card, yellow glow effect","fine tune ai model,lora training,small language model,gpu training,ai model training,quantization,gguf,ollama,specialized ai,mini models,consumer gpu training,ai on budget,model fine tuning,gemma2,phi3,local ai,open source ai,model optimization,ai training tutorial,stacked models","How we trained 13 specialized AI models on a single consumer GPU using LoRA and quantization — and why they beat giant models.","Get our training recipe and dataset templates — free download below!","TikTok, LinkedIn, Blog Post"),
    _s("Build Your Own AI Content Factory in One Weekend","YouTube","20:00","Stop paying for content. Start producing it.","1. The content factory concept\n2. Setting up the pipeline\n3. Script generation with local AI\n4. Automated editing workflow\n5. Publishing and scheduling","What if you could produce 30 pieces of content per day without hiring anyone? That is exactly what we built and today I am giving you the entire blueprint. We call it the Content Factory. It starts with one script generated by a fine-tuned AI model. That script becomes a YouTube video, a TikTok, an Instagram Reel, a blog post, a tweet thread, an email newsletter, and a podcast clip. Seven outputs from one input. The entire system runs on a single server. No API costs. No subscriptions. Just open-source tools stitched together intelligently.","Factory assembly line animation, content pieces flowing out, dashboard views, before/after metrics","Factory building with conveyor belt, content pieces (video/blog/tweet icons) coming out the other end","ai content factory,content automation,content repurposing,automated content,ai content creation,content pipeline,bulk content,content at scale,ai writing,video to blog,repurpose content,content marketing ai,social media automation,content strategy,ai workflow,content machine,automated posting,content calendar,ai producer,content empire","Build a complete AI content factory that turns one script into 7 pieces of content — all running locally with no API costs.","Download the Content Factory setup guide — link in description!","TikTok, Instagram Reels, Blog Post, LinkedIn"),
    _s("Running AI Models on a Mac Mini Cluster","YouTube","15:00","Forget cloud costs. Build your own inference cluster for under two thousand dollars.","1. Why Apple Silicon for AI inference\n2. The Mac Mini cluster setup\n3. Unified memory advantage\n4. Distributed inference with exo\n5. Cost comparison vs cloud","Cloud AI costs are insane. We are talking hundreds to thousands per month for inference. But there is a secret the big companies do not want you to know. You can build your own AI inference cluster using Mac Minis for a one-time cost of under two thousand dollars. Apple Silicon has unified memory which means the GPU can access all the RAM. Two Mac Mini M2s with 24 gigs each gives you 48 gigs of pooled memory through a tool called exo. That is enough to run 30 billion parameter models locally. Zero monthly cost after purchase.","Mac Mini unboxing, cluster setup timelapse, exo dashboard, performance benchmarks, cost comparison charts","Two Mac Minis connected with glowing data streams, AI brain hologram floating above, dark background","mac mini ai,apple silicon ai,ai cluster,local inference,exo distributed,mac mini cluster,unified memory,ai on mac,cheap ai inference,no cloud ai,self hosted ai,mac mini m2,ai hardware,inference cluster,distributed llm,local llm,apple ai,mac ai setup,budget ai cluster,ai infrastructure","Build a Mac Mini AI inference cluster for under $2000 that runs 30B+ parameter models with zero monthly cloud costs.","Watch our full Mac cluster build guide — playlist link below!","TikTok, LinkedIn, Blog Post"),
])
SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-business"].extend([
    _s("How to Price AI Services Without Underselling Yourself","YouTube","11:00","Most AI freelancers charge too little. Here is the framework that fixes that.","1. The value-based pricing model\n2. Calculating ROI for clients\n3. Tier structure that works\n4. Handling price objections\n5. When to walk away","If you are charging hourly for AI services you are leaving money on the table. The client does not care how long it takes you. They care about the result. A chatbot that saves them 40 hours per month is worth way more than your 10 hours of building it. Today I will teach you value-based pricing for AI services. We use a four-tier model ranging from 297 to 2997 per month. Each tier is designed around client outcomes not your time. This framework has helped us close five-figure contracts consistently.","Pricing spreadsheet, client meeting footage, proposal templates, calculator animations","Price tag with AI circuit pattern, four ascending tiers shown as steps, gold and dark theme","ai pricing,ai services pricing,value based pricing,ai freelance,ai consulting,ai agency pricing,how to price ai,ai business model,ai saas pricing,consulting rates,ai contractor,freelance ai,ai service tiers,pricing strategy,ai proposals,client pricing,ai revenue model,sell ai services,ai pricing framework,charge more ai","Learn the value-based pricing framework for AI services that helps you charge what you are worth.","Download our AI pricing calculator template — link below!","TikTok, LinkedIn, Blog Post"),
    _s("Building a Service Business That Runs Without You","YouTube","16:00","The goal is not to work IN your business. It is to work ON it.","1. Systems over hustle\n2. Automating dispatch and scheduling\n3. AI-powered customer communication\n4. Financial dashboards that update themselves\n5. The owner's weekly 4-hour check","I used to work 80 hours a week in my service business. Now it runs in 4 hours per week. The difference is not working harder. It is building systems. Every repeatable task gets automated. Dispatch is handled by AI. Customer communication runs through chatbots and automated texts. Financial reports generate themselves. Today I will show you the exact systems we built to make a service business run autonomously. This is not theory. These systems handle real jobs every day.","Business dashboard, automation flowcharts, before/after owner schedule, system architecture","Business owner relaxing while robots handle tasks, split screen with chaos vs organized","automated business,business systems,service business automation,run business without you,business automation,ai for business,dispatch automation,autonomous business,systemize business,business owner freedom,passive business,automated scheduling,ai customer service,business dashboard,service company automation,small business systems,business efficiency,work less earn more,business freedom,automated operations","How to build systems that let your service business run without you — from 80 hours to 4 hours per week.","Get our Business Automation Checklist — free download in description!","TikTok, LinkedIn, Instagram Reels"),
    _s("The AI Agency Model That Actually Works","YouTube","13:00","Everyone is starting AI agencies. Here is why most fail and how to be different.","1. Why most AI agencies fail in 6 months\n2. The productized service model\n3. Finding your niche\n4. Delivering repeatable results\n5. Scaling with systems not people","The AI agency space is exploding but 90 percent of new agencies fail within 6 months. The reason is simple. They try to be everything to everyone. They take any project any client and burn out trying to deliver custom solutions every time. The agencies that succeed do one thing. They productize. Pick one industry. Solve one problem. Build the solution once and deploy it many times. We chose local service businesses. We deploy AI phone agents and content engines. Same stack every time. Different branding. That is how you scale.","Agency dashboard, client onboarding flow, revenue growth chart, niche selection framework","Agency storefront with AI products on shelves, assembly line deploying to different businesses","ai agency,start ai agency,ai agency model,productized service,ai consulting,ai business,scale ai agency,ai niche,ai for local business,ai agency 2026,ai service business,ai startup,agency model,ai freelance to agency,ai agency revenue,build ai agency,ai agency clients,ai agency pricing,ai agency tips,successful ai agency","The productized AI agency model that works — pick one niche, solve one problem, deploy many times.","Join our AI Agency Builder community — link in description!","TikTok, LinkedIn, Blog Post"),
    _s("5 Revenue Streams Every AI Business Needs","YouTube","10:00","One income source is a risk. Five is a fortress.","1. Done-for-you services\n2. SaaS subscriptions\n3. Training and courses\n4. Affiliate and referral\n5. White-label licensing","Relying on one revenue stream is the fastest way to kill your AI business. Client work dries up. Contracts end. Markets shift. You need multiple streams flowing simultaneously. Stream one is done-for-you services. High touch high margin. Stream two is SaaS subscriptions. Recurring revenue that compounds monthly. Stream three is training and courses. Package your expertise once sell it forever. Stream four is affiliate and referral income. Recommend tools you already use. Stream five is white-label licensing. Let other agencies resell your tech under their brand.","Revenue stream diagrams, income pie charts, example dashboards for each stream","Five water streams flowing into one large river, each labeled with a revenue type, blue and gold theme","ai revenue streams,multiple income ai,ai business revenue,ai saas,ai consulting,ai courses,ai affiliate,white label ai,diversify income,ai business model,recurring revenue ai,ai passive income,ai monetization,make money ai business,ai income sources,ai entrepreneur revenue,business diversification,ai product revenue,ai licensing,ai business growth","The 5 essential revenue streams every AI business needs to survive and thrive long-term.","Download our Revenue Stream Planner — link in description!","TikTok, LinkedIn, Blog Post"),
    _s("From Side Hustle to Six Figures with AI","YouTube","14:00","I went from zero to six figures in 8 months using AI. Here is the exact path.","1. Month 1-2: Learning and building\n2. Month 3-4: First paying clients\n3. Month 5-6: Systemizing and scaling\n4. Month 7-8: Team and automation\n5. Key mistakes to avoid","Eight months ago I had zero AI clients and zero recurring revenue. Today we are crossing six figures annually and growing every month. This is not a get-rich-quick story. This is a systematic approach to building an AI business from scratch. Month one and two were pure learning and building. I trained models, built prototypes, and gave away free work to build a portfolio. Month three and four I landed my first three paying clients through cold outreach. Month five and six I systemized everything so I could handle ten clients without ten times the work. Let me walk you through every step.","Timeline infographic, revenue growth chart, milestone markers, real client testimonials","Staircase with monthly markers, person climbing from $0 to $100K, AI elements on each step","ai side hustle,six figures ai,ai business journey,grow ai business,ai freelance to agency,ai income growth,ai business timeline,first ai clients,scale ai business,ai entrepreneur story,ai business tips,ai consulting growth,ai revenue growth,zero to six figures,ai career,ai business plan,build ai business,ai success story,ai business scaling,monthly revenue ai","The exact 8-month path from zero AI clients to six figures in annual recurring revenue.","Get our AI Business Roadmap template — free in description!","TikTok, Instagram Reels, LinkedIn"),
])
SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-money"].extend([
    _s("Algorithmic Trading on a Budget — What Actually Works","YouTube","15:00","You do not need Bloomberg terminals. You need a strategy and a cheap VPS.","1. Realistic expectations for retail algo trading\n2. The tech stack that costs under 50 per month\n3. Building a simple momentum strategy\n4. Backtesting properly\n5. Risk management rules that save accounts","Wall Street spends billions on trading infrastructure. You can build a profitable algo trading system for under 50 dollars a month. I am not talking about beating hedge funds. I am talking about consistent small gains that compound over time. Our USD/JPY scalper runs on a basic VPS with a Python script. It watches price action, identifies momentum, and executes trades with strict stop losses. The key is not prediction. It is risk management. A 3 pip stop loss and 6 pip take profit with 55 percent accuracy is profitable. Let me show you the math and the code.","Trading charts, code editor, backtesting results, P&L curves, VPS dashboard","Trading chart with Python code overlay, small budget wallet icon, green profit line going up","algo trading budget,cheap algo trading,retail trading,python trading bot,forex algorithm,momentum strategy,backtesting,risk management trading,usdjpy scalper,trading vps,automated trading,trading bot python,forex bot,algorithmic trading tutorial,budget trading,home trader,diy trading bot,trading risk management,small account trading,compound trading","How to build a profitable algorithmic trading system on a budget of under $50/month with Python.","Download our trading bot starter template — link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post, LinkedIn"),
    _s("The Compound Effect: How Small Daily Gains Build Wealth","YouTube","10:00","One percent per day does not sound like much. Until you do the math.","1. The math behind compounding\n2. Daily habits that compound\n3. Investment strategies that compound\n4. Skill compounding for income growth\n5. The patience factor","If you improve by just one percent every day for a year you end up 37 times better. That is not motivation. That is math. Compounding works the same way in your finances. Small consistent gains beat big risky bets every single time. Our trading algorithm does not try to hit home runs. It targets small consistent wins with tight risk management. The same principle applies to saving investing and skill building. A 0.5 percent daily trading gain compounded over 200 trading days turns 10 thousand into over 27 thousand. But only if you protect the downside.","Compound growth charts, daily vs monthly comparison, calculator animations, snowball rolling downhill","Small snowball at top rolling down mountain becoming massive, dollar signs growing exponentially","compound effect,compounding,daily gains,wealth building,compound interest,small gains big results,investing compounding,trading compounding,1 percent daily,exponential growth,patience investing,long term wealth,compound returns,daily improvement,financial growth,compound trading,snowball effect,wealth accumulation,consistent gains,compound formula","How small daily gains of just 1% compound into extraordinary results over time — in trading, investing, and life.","Get our Compound Growth Calculator — free in description!","TikTok, Instagram Reels, Blog Post"),
    _s("Passive Income Streams That Actually Work in 2026","YouTube","13:00","Forget dropshipping. These streams require work upfront but pay forever.","1. AI SaaS products on auto-pilot\n2. Dividend investing for cash flow\n3. Digital product libraries\n4. Automated affiliate sites\n5. Licensing your AI models","Passive income is not about doing nothing. It is about doing the work once and getting paid repeatedly. The best passive income streams in 2026 all share one trait. They are digital and scalable. Stream one is AI SaaS. Build a tool once and charge monthly subscriptions. Stream two is dividend investing. Not exciting but reliable. Stream three is digital products. Templates, courses, datasets. Create once and sell forever. Stream four is automated affiliate sites powered by AI content. Stream five is licensing your trained AI models to other businesses. We do all five.","Income dashboard, dividend portfolio, SaaS metrics, digital product storefront, licensing agreement","Five money faucets dripping into a large pool, each labeled, relaxing beach background","passive income 2026,passive income streams,ai passive income,dividend investing,digital products,ai saas,affiliate income,license ai models,recurring revenue,automated income,passive income ideas,real passive income,income streams,make money sleeping,digital income,saas revenue,passive business,income automation,wealth building,financial freedom","5 passive income streams that actually work in 2026 — all digital, all scalable, all proven.","Download our Passive Income Planner — link in description!","TikTok, Instagram Reels, LinkedIn"),
    _s("How to Read a Forex Chart in 5 Minutes","YouTube Shorts","0:58","Stop guessing. Start reading.","1. Candlesticks\n2. Support/resistance\n3. Moving averages\n4. Volume\n5. Trend direction","Reading a forex chart is simpler than you think. Candlesticks show you price action. Green means buyers won. Red means sellers won. The wicks show rejection. Support is where price bounces up. Resistance is where it bounces down. The 20 EMA shows you the trend. Price above it means bullish. Below means bearish. Volume confirms the move. High volume on a breakout means it is real. That is 90 percent of chart reading in under a minute. Practice on USD/JPY. It is the cleanest pair to learn on.","Annotated charts, candlestick close-ups, drawing support/resistance lines","Clean forex chart with big annotations pointing to each element, bright colors on dark background","forex chart reading,how to read charts,candlestick chart,forex for beginners,support resistance,moving average,forex tutorial,chart analysis,technical analysis,trading charts,forex basics,learn forex,usdjpy chart,chart patterns,forex education,trading education,price action,chart reading tutorial,forex tips,beginner trading","Learn to read a forex chart in under 60 seconds — candlesticks, support/resistance, moving averages, and volume.","Follow for more trading tips!","TikTok, Instagram Reels"),
])
SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-code"].extend([
    _s("Build a Full REST API in Python Under 100 Lines","YouTube","12:00","You do not need Django. You need aiohttp and 100 lines of Python.","1. Why aiohttp over Flask/Django\n2. Setting up routes\n3. Database integration\n4. Error handling\n5. Deployment","Most API tutorials make it way too complicated. You do not need a massive framework with dozens of dependencies. Today I am building a complete REST API in under 100 lines of Python using aiohttp. It will have CRUD operations, SQLite database integration, proper error handling, and CORS support. The whole thing runs on a single file. No virtual environments needed for development. Copy paste and it works. This is the same pattern we use for every microservice in our production system. Over 30 services all using this exact template.","Code editor with syntax highlighting, terminal running tests, API endpoint testing in browser","Terminal screen with clean Python code, 100 written in large text, API endpoints listed","python api,rest api python,aiohttp tutorial,python microservice,100 lines api,simple api,python backend,api tutorial,build api,python web server,aiohttp api,lightweight api,python rest,api development,python server,fast api alternative,minimal api,python crud,sqlite api,single file api","Build a production-ready REST API in under 100 lines of Python using aiohttp — no bloated frameworks needed.","Get the API template code — GitHub link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post, LinkedIn"),
    _s("SQLite Is All You Need — Why We Ditched Postgres","YouTube","11:00","We run 40 databases on SQLite. Here is why it is better for most projects.","1. When SQLite beats Postgres\n2. WAL mode for concurrency\n3. Backup is just copying a file\n4. Performance benchmarks\n5. When you actually need Postgres","Hot take. For 90 percent of applications SQLite is better than Postgres. We run over 40 SQLite databases in production and they handle everything from trading data to CRM to content management. The advantages are massive. Zero configuration. Backup means copying a file. No server process eating RAM. WAL mode handles concurrent reads beautifully. We have databases with 500 thousand rows that query in milliseconds. The only time you need Postgres is when you have hundreds of concurrent writers or need distributed replication. For everything else SQLite wins.","Benchmark comparisons, database file sizes, query speed tests, architecture diagram","SQLite logo large and golden vs faded Postgres logo, VS text in the middle, dark background","sqlite vs postgres,sqlite production,sqlite database,why sqlite,database choice,sqlite wal mode,sqlite performance,sqlite tutorial,simple database,embedded database,sqlite python,database backup,sqlite concurrency,lightweight database,sqlite advantages,no database server,file database,sqlite benchmarks,database comparison,sqlite best practices","Why SQLite is the right database for 90% of applications — and how we run 40 databases on it in production.","Download our SQLite best practices guide — link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post, LinkedIn"),
    _s("Systemd Services: Deploy Any Python Script as a Service","YouTube","9:00","Your script should survive reboots. Here is how to make it bulletproof.","1. Writing a systemd unit file\n2. Auto-restart on crash\n3. Logging with journalctl\n4. Environment variables\n5. Multi-service orchestration","You wrote a Python script that needs to run 24/7. How do you deploy it? Docker? Kubernetes? No. Systemd. It is already on your Linux server. It is battle-tested. It is simple. A systemd service file is 10 lines that tell Linux to run your script, restart it if it crashes, and start it on boot. We run over 30 services this way. Each one has auto-restart, proper logging through journalctl, environment variable injection, and dependency ordering. Today I will show you the exact template we use for every service and how to manage them like a pro.","Terminal with systemd commands, service file editing, journalctl output, service status dashboard","Terminal showing systemctl status with green active dots, Python logo, Linux penguin","systemd python,deploy python,python service,systemd tutorial,linux service,python daemon,systemd unit file,auto restart python,journalctl,python deployment,server python,production python,systemd service file,linux python,deploy script,python 24/7,always running python,systemctl tutorial,service management,python ops","How to deploy any Python script as a systemd service that auto-restarts and survives reboots.","Get our systemd service template — link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post"),
    _s("SSH Tunnels and Tailscale: Secure Networking for Hackers","YouTube","13:00","Your home lab should be accessible from anywhere. Securely.","1. The problem with port forwarding\n2. SSH tunnels explained\n3. Tailscale mesh networking\n4. Cloudflare tunnels for public access\n5. Zero-trust architecture at home","Port forwarding is a security nightmare. You are punching holes in your firewall and hoping nobody finds them. There is a better way. SSH tunnels encrypt traffic between machines without exposing ports. But for a permanent mesh network Tailscale is the answer. Install it on every machine and they can all talk to each other over encrypted WireGuard tunnels. No port forwarding. No firewall rules. Just secure connections. We run a 5 machine mesh this way. For public services we add Cloudflare tunnels which give us HTTPS domains pointing to internal services without exposing a single port.","Network diagrams, Tailscale admin console, tunnel setup commands, before/after architecture","Mesh network with 5 nodes connected by glowing secure tunnels, lock icons on connections","ssh tunnels,tailscale,mesh networking,secure networking,cloudflare tunnel,port forwarding alternative,wireguard,home lab networking,zero trust,network security,ssh tutorial,tailscale tutorial,homelab,secure home server,vpn alternative,network mesh,private network,remote access,secure connections,devops networking","Secure your home lab with SSH tunnels, Tailscale mesh networking, and Cloudflare tunnels — no port forwarding needed.","Try Tailscale free — link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post, LinkedIn"),
    _s("Git for Solo Developers: The Only Commands You Need","YouTube","8:00","You do not need to know 50 git commands. You need these 7.","1. git init and clone\n2. git add and commit\n3. git push and pull\n4. git branch and checkout\n5. git stash\n6. git log\n7. git diff","Git tutorials always overcomplicate things. If you are a solo developer you need exactly 7 commands. Init creates a repo. Add stages files. Commit saves a snapshot. Push sends it to GitHub. Pull gets updates. Branch creates a parallel version. Stash temporarily saves work in progress. That is it. I have been coding for years and use these 7 commands for 99 percent of my git workflow. Today I will show you each one with real examples and the exact aliases I use to type them faster. Stop memorizing commands and start shipping code.","Terminal with git commands, visual branch diagrams, commit history visualization","Git logo with 7 command boxes arranged around it, clean minimal design, dark background","git tutorial,git for beginners,git commands,solo developer git,git basics,learn git,git workflow,git essentials,git cheat sheet,simple git,git init,git commit,git push,git branch,developer tools,coding basics,version control,github tutorial,git shortcuts,git aliases","The only 7 git commands solo developers actually need — stop overcomplicating version control.","Download our Git cheat sheet — link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post"),
])
SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-build"].extend([
    _s("Setting Up a Home Server for AI on a $500 Budget","YouTube","16:00","You do not need AWS. You need a used desktop and Linux.","1. Hardware selection on a budget\n2. Linux installation and setup\n3. Installing Ollama for local AI\n4. Setting up services with systemd\n5. Remote access with Tailscale","Cloud computing is eating your wallet. Every month another bill for GPU instances you barely use. The solution is a home server. For 500 dollars or less you can build a machine that runs AI models 24/7 with zero monthly cost. Start with a used desktop. A Ryzen 5 with 32 gigs of RAM costs about 300 used. Add a used GTX 1660 Super for 100 bucks. That gives you 6 gigs of VRAM which runs 7 billion parameter models easily. Install Ubuntu Server. Add Ollama for AI inference. Set up Tailscale for remote access. Done. You now have your own AI cloud.","Hardware shopping, unboxing, Ubuntu installation, Ollama running, htop showing system stats","Budget PC build with parts laid out, price tags visible, AI brain hologram coming from the case","home server,ai server,budget server,home lab,ollama setup,linux server,self hosted ai,cheap ai server,local ai,gtx 1660 ai,home cloud,diy server,ai on budget,ubuntu server,home ai setup,server build,ai hardware,self hosted,tailscale server,ai infrastructure","Build a home AI server for under $500 that runs language models 24/7 with zero monthly cloud costs.","Get our Home Server Build List — link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post, LinkedIn"),
    _s("Cable Management That Does Not Suck","YouTube Shorts","0:55","Your server rack looks like spaghetti. Fix it in 10 minutes.","1. Velcro over zip ties\n2. Color coding by function\n3. Service loops\n4. Label everything\n5. Route then connect","Stop using zip ties. Velcro straps let you add and remove cables without cutting. Color code by function. Blue for network. Yellow for power. Red for management. Leave service loops so you can pull equipment without disconnecting. Label both ends of every cable. And the golden rule. Route first then connect. Never plug in a cable before routing it through your management. Ten minutes of cable management saves hours of troubleshooting. Clean cables mean fewer accidents and faster maintenance. Your future self will thank you.","Before/after cable management shots, close-ups of velcro straps, labeled cables","Split screen: messy cables vs perfectly managed rack, satisfying transformation","cable management,server rack,clean cables,cable organization,velcro cable ties,server setup,network cables,rack management,homelab cables,cable routing,organized server,cable labels,cable management tips,server maintenance,clean server,rack cable management,it cable management,network rack,cable management hacks,satisfying cables","5 cable management tips that transform your server rack from spaghetti to perfection in 10 minutes.","Follow for more home lab tips!","TikTok, Instagram Reels"),
    _s("Monitoring Your Home Lab with Zero Cost Tools","YouTube","12:00","You do not need Datadog. You need a shell script and common sense.","1. htop and btop for system monitoring\n2. Custom health check scripts\n3. SQLite for metrics storage\n4. Simple web dashboards\n5. Alert system via Telegram","Enterprise monitoring tools cost hundreds per month and most of them are overkill for a home lab. We monitor five machines with 30 plus services using nothing but shell scripts and Python. Htop shows real-time system stats. Custom health check scripts ping every service every 5 minutes. Results go into SQLite. A simple Python web server shows a dashboard. If anything dies we get a Telegram alert instantly. Total cost zero dollars. The system has caught server issues at 3 AM multiple times. When something goes down the watchdog auto-restarts it and notifies us. That is enterprise-grade monitoring for free.","Dashboard screenshots, terminal monitoring, Telegram alert notifications, system architecture diagram","Monitor screens showing green status indicators, dark command center aesthetic, zero dollar price tag","home lab monitoring,free monitoring,server monitoring,health checks,system monitoring,diy monitoring,no datadog,telegram alerts,python monitoring,watchdog script,auto restart,service monitoring,home server,infrastructure monitoring,monitoring dashboard,free devops,budget monitoring,self hosted monitoring,system health,monitoring tools","Monitor your entire home lab for $0 using shell scripts, Python health checks, and Telegram alerts.","Get our monitoring script templates — GitHub link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post"),
    _s("Power Backup for Home Servers: UPS Guide","YouTube","8:00","One power outage can corrupt your databases. Protect them for 50 bucks.","1. Why home servers need UPS\n2. Choosing the right capacity\n3. USB monitoring with apcupsd\n4. Graceful shutdown scripts\n5. Battery maintenance","A power outage hit my home lab last month. No UPS. Three databases corrupted. Two days of recovery. Never again. A basic UPS costs 50 to 100 dollars and it is the most important investment for any home server. It gives you 10 to 15 minutes of battery power. More importantly it gives your servers time for a graceful shutdown. With apcupsd your Linux machine detects when power goes out and runs a shutdown script automatically. That script closes databases cleanly, stops services, and powers off safely. Your data survives intact. Fifty dollars of prevention versus days of recovery.","UPS unboxing, apcupsd dashboard, power outage simulation, database corruption recovery","UPS unit protecting a glowing server, lightning bolt being blocked by a shield","ups home server,power backup,apcupsd,server ups,home lab ups,power outage protection,ups guide,battery backup server,graceful shutdown,database protection,ups monitoring,linux ups,server power,homelab power,ups setup,power protection,battery backup,ups for computers,server safety,ups buying guide","Protect your home servers from power outages with a $50 UPS and automated graceful shutdown scripts.","Check our recommended UPS units — affiliate links in description!","TikTok, Blog Post"),
])
SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-locksmith"].extend([
    _s("What to Do When Your Key Breaks Inside the Lock","YouTube Shorts","0:50","Do NOT try to dig it out with tweezers. You will make it worse.","1. Stop and assess\n2. Try the extraction tool method\n3. Spray lubricant\n4. When to call a pro\n5. Prevention tips","Your key just snapped inside the lock. Do not panic. And do not grab tweezers or pliers because you will push the broken piece deeper. Step one spray WD-40 or graphite lubricant into the keyhole. Step two get a broken key extractor tool. They cost 5 dollars on Amazon. Slide it along the broken piece and twist to grip the teeth. Pull straight out slowly. If the key is too deep or you cannot grip it call a locksmith. A pro extraction takes 5 minutes and costs about 75 dollars. Trying to force it yourself can damage the lock cylinder which turns a 75 dollar fix into a 250 dollar replacement.","Close-up of broken key, extraction tool demonstration, lock cylinder cutaway","Broken key stuck in lock close-up, with solution steps overlaid, red to green color progression","broken key,key stuck in lock,key extraction,broken key removal,locksmith tips,lock fix,broken key in door,emergency locksmith,key broke,lock repair,broken key extractor,locksmith tutorial,key removal,stuck key,lock cylinder,key broke in lock,diy lock fix,locksmith hack,key extraction tool,lock emergency","What to do when your key breaks inside the lock — and the one mistake that makes it 3x more expensive.","Save this for emergencies! Follow for more locksmith tips.","TikTok, Instagram Reels"),
    _s("Smart Lock vs Traditional Lock: Which Is Actually Safer?","YouTube","10:00","Smart locks are convenient. But are they actually more secure?","1. Physical security comparison\n2. Hacking vulnerabilities in smart locks\n3. Battery failure risks\n4. Key override options\n5. Our recommendation","Everyone is switching to smart locks but nobody talks about the security tradeoffs. A traditional deadbolt has one attack vector. Physical force. A smart lock has three. Physical force, electronic hacking, and battery failure. Most smart locks use Bluetooth which can be sniffed and replayed. WiFi models can be attacked remotely. And when the battery dies you are locked out unless there is a key override. That said good smart locks with encryption and key backup are reasonably secure for residential use. But for commercial properties we always recommend high-security traditional locks. Here is our honest breakdown.","Smart lock teardown, hacking demonstration, security comparison chart, installation footage","Smart lock and traditional deadbolt facing off, shield icons comparing security features","smart lock vs traditional,smart lock security,are smart locks safe,smart lock hacking,bluetooth lock,wifi lock,keypad lock,traditional deadbolt,lock comparison,home security,smart lock review,lock safety,electronic lock,smart home security,best lock,lock buying guide,smart lock problems,lock security,residential locks,commercial locks","Smart lock vs traditional deadbolt — an honest security comparison from a professional locksmith.","Need a lock assessment? Book a free consultation — link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post, Instagram Reels"),
    _s("5 Signs Your Locks Need to Be Changed Right Now","YouTube Shorts","0:58","Number 3 means someone may already have a copy of your key.","1. Lock is loose or wobbly\n2. Key sticks or needs jiggling\n3. You just moved into a new place\n4. Visible rust or corrosion\n5. You cannot remember who has copies","Five signs you need new locks right now. Number one your lock is loose or wobbly. That means the screws or cylinder are worn. Easy to force open. Number two your key sticks or needs jiggling. The pins inside are worn and the lock is failing. Number three you just moved into a new place. The previous owner and their friends family and contractors all have copies. Number four visible rust or corrosion. A corroded lock can fail or get stuck when you need it most. Number five you cannot remember who has copies of your key. If you cannot track every copy it is time for new locks. Rekeying starts at 50 dollars per lock.","Close-up shots of each problem sign, before/after lock replacement, rekeying demonstration","Five warning signs with lock images, red alert icons, numbered list overlay","change locks,rekey locks,lock replacement,lock safety,home security,when to change locks,worn lock,moving new locks,lock signs,locksmith advice,door lock,deadbolt replacement,lock maintenance,new home locks,lock security check,lock inspection,lock problems,rekey vs replace,lock wear signs,home lock upgrade","5 warning signs your locks need immediate replacement — number 3 is a security emergency most people ignore.","Book a lock assessment — link in bio!","TikTok, Instagram Reels"),
])
SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-home"].extend([
    _s("5 Home Security Mistakes That Make Break-Ins Easy","YouTube","10:00","Burglars look for these exact things before choosing a target.","1. Hiding keys in obvious spots\n2. Leaving garage door openers visible\n3. Social media travel posts\n4. Poor outdoor lighting\n5. Unlocked windows","A former burglar once told me that 60 percent of break-ins happen through unlocked doors and windows. You do not need a fancy alarm system. You need to stop making these five mistakes. Mistake one is hiding your spare key under the mat, in a fake rock, or above the door frame. Burglars check all of these first. Mistake two is leaving your garage door opener visible in your car. That is literally a button that opens your house. Mistake three is posting vacation photos on social media while you are still gone. That tells everyone your house is empty. Mistake four is poor outdoor lighting. Darkness is a burglar's best friend. Mistake five is unlocked windows especially on the ground floor.","Home exterior shots, hiding spot demonstrations, lighting comparison, security audit walkthrough","House with 5 red X marks on common mistakes, burglar silhouette in background, warning theme","home security mistakes,break in prevention,burglar tips,home security,lock your doors,home safety,security tips,prevent break ins,home protection,burglar proof,home security audit,door locks,window locks,outdoor lighting,smart security,home safety tips,security mistakes,protect your home,residential security,crime prevention","5 common home security mistakes that make your house an easy target for break-ins — and how to fix each one.","Get our free Home Security Checklist — link in description!","TikTok, Instagram Reels, Blog Post"),
    _s("The Best Smart Home Devices Under $50","YouTube","12:00","You do not need to spend thousands. These devices transform your home for cheap.","1. Smart plugs for automation\n2. Motion sensor lights\n3. Door/window sensors\n4. Smart bulbs\n5. WiFi cameras","Smart home does not mean expensive home. You can automate and secure your entire house for under 250 dollars total with devices that cost under 50 each. Smart plugs at 15 dollars each let you automate any appliance. Turn on lights at sunset. Start the coffee maker at 6 AM. Motion sensor lights at 20 dollars keep your property lit without wasting electricity. Door and window sensors at 10 dollars alert your phone when something opens. Smart bulbs at 12 dollars set the mood and simulate presence when you are away. And WiFi cameras at 30 dollars give you 24/7 monitoring with cloud recording. All controlled from your phone.","Unboxing each device, installation demos, phone app walkthroughs, automation setup","Five smart devices arranged on a table with price tags under $50, smart home background","smart home budget,cheap smart home,smart home under 50,smart plugs,motion lights,door sensors,smart bulbs,wifi camera,home automation,budget smart home,smart home devices,home automation cheap,affordable smart home,smart home setup,best smart devices,smart home deals,smart home starter,home tech,iot devices,smart home beginners","Transform your home with 5 smart devices all under $50 each — automation, security, and convenience on a budget.","Check our recommended devices — affiliate links in description!","TikTok, Instagram Reels, Blog Post"),
    _s("DIY vs Professional: When to Call an Expert","YouTube","9:00","Some jobs save money doing yourself. Others cost triple when you mess up.","1. Safe DIY projects\n2. Dangerous DIY attempts\n3. Cost comparison\n4. Liability and insurance\n5. The 80/20 rule of home repair","DIY culture is great but it has a dark side. Every week I get calls from homeowners who tried to fix something themselves and made it worse. There are two categories. Category one is safe DIY. Painting. Basic plumbing like changing faucets. Replacing outlets and switches if you know electrical safety. Simple lock changes. Category two is call a pro. Anything structural. Main electrical panel work. Gas lines. Roof repair. And rekeying high-security locks. The 80/20 rule applies. 80 percent of home repairs are safe to DIY. But that 20 percent can injure you, void insurance, or cost triple to fix after a botched attempt.","DIY fails compilation, professional vs amateur comparison, cost breakdown charts","Split screen: happy DIY on left, disaster DIY on right, money flying away from the disaster side","diy vs professional,when to call pro,home repair diy,diy mistakes,home repair tips,hire professional,diy saves money,home maintenance,diy home repair,professional repair,home improvement,diy risks,home repair cost,diy or hire,home project tips,repair yourself,contractor vs diy,home fix,diy fail,home repair guide","When to DIY and when to call a professional — the 80/20 rule that saves money and prevents disasters.","Download our DIY Decision Guide — link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post"),
])
SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-podcast"].extend([
    _s("The Future of Work Is Agents, Not Apps","Podcast","25:00","Software is about to get fired. AI agents are taking its job.","1. Why apps are broken\n2. The agent paradigm shift\n3. Real-world agent examples\n4. Building agent systems\n5. What this means for developers","Every decade we get a new computing paradigm. Mainframes. PCs. Web. Mobile. Cloud. The next one is agents. Not apps that wait for you to click buttons. Agents that go do things for you. Think about booking a flight. Today you open an app, search, compare, filter, select, fill in forms, pay. With agents you say book me a flight to Miami next Tuesday morning cheapest option. The agent does everything. It searches multiple airlines. Compares prices. Books the best option. Sends you the confirmation. The interface is conversation not buttons. This changes everything for how software is built and how businesses operate.","None — podcast audio only","Microphone with AI circuit patterns, FUTURE OF WORK text, agent robot icons replacing app icons","ai agents,future of work,software agents,agent paradigm,ai apps,autonomous agents,ai automation,future technology,agent ai,software evolution,ai workforce,digital agents,ai assistants,task agents,agent systems,ai paradigm shift,post-app era,conversational ai,agent framework,ai future","Deep dive into why AI agents will replace traditional apps and what it means for the future of software and work.","Subscribe to the podcast for weekly AI insights!","YouTube, Blog Post, LinkedIn"),
    _s("Why Small Models Will Win the AI War","Podcast","20:00","Everyone is chasing bigger models. The smart money is going smaller.","1. The diminishing returns of scale\n2. Specialized vs general models\n3. Deployment economics\n4. Edge AI advantages\n5. Our stacked mini-model results","The AI industry has an obsession with bigger models. GPT-5 will have a trillion parameters. Gemini Ultra is massive. But there is a counter-trend happening quietly and it is going to win. Small specialized models. A 2 billion parameter model fine-tuned on locksmith phone calls outperforms GPT-4 for that specific task. It costs nothing to run. It starts in 2 seconds. It runs on a laptop. And you own it. No API costs. No rate limits. No data privacy concerns. We run 13 specialized models on a single consumer GPU. Each one is an expert in its domain. That is the future. Not one god model but an army of specialists.","None — podcast audio only","David vs Goliath scene with small model beating big model, brain icons of different sizes","small ai models,specialized models,fine tuned models,ai efficiency,small language models,model size,ai economics,edge ai,local ai models,mini models,ai deployment,model training,efficient ai,ai cost,gpt alternative,local llm,ollama models,ai strategy,model optimization,ai war","Why small specialized AI models are beating giant ones — and how we run 13 experts on a single GPU.","Download our model training guide — link in description!","YouTube, Blog Post, LinkedIn"),
    _s("Zero to Hive: Building an AI Empire from Scratch","Podcast","30:00","This is the story of how we built a 50-service AI system from nothing.","1. The early days — one script on one machine\n2. Growing pains — when things break at scale\n3. The mesh network evolution\n4. Revenue attempts and failures\n5. Where we are going next","A year ago this was one Python script on one laptop. Today it is 50 services running across 5 machines with over 500 Python files processing real phone calls, trading forex, generating content, and managing a local service business. This episode is the full unfiltered story. The wins and the failures. The 3 AM debugging sessions. The time the server froze at load 37 because we ran too many processes. The moment our AI phone agent had its first real conversation with a customer. The trading bot that lost money before we fixed the risk management. Building in public means sharing everything. So here it is. Everything.","None — podcast audio only","Hive honeycomb growing from a single cell to massive structure, time-lapse style, golden theme","ai empire,building ai,startup story,ai system,ai infrastructure,from scratch ai,hive system,ai agents,multi service ai,ai journey,building in public,ai startup,home lab ai,ai architecture,ai growth,solo builder,ai entrepreneur,system building,ai mesh,ai evolution","The complete story of building a 50-service AI empire from one Python script — wins, failures, and everything in between.","Subscribe for the next chapter of the Hive story!","YouTube, Blog Post"),
])
SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-creative"].extend([
    _s("Color Theory for Tech Content Creators","YouTube","11:00","Your thumbnails look amateur because of one thing. Color.","1. The color wheel basics\n2. Complementary vs analogous schemes\n3. Colors that get clicks\n4. Brand color consistency\n5. Tools for color selection","The difference between a thumbnail that gets clicked and one that gets ignored is often just color. Color theory is not just for artists. It is a science of attention. Complementary colors create contrast that pops. Red text on a blue background catches the eye. Yellow against purple screams urgency. The YouTube algorithm does not see color but humans do and humans decide what to click. We tested this across our 10 channels. Thumbnails with high contrast complementary colors got 40 percent more clicks than low contrast ones. Same content. Same titles. Just better colors. Here are the exact hex codes and combinations we use.","Color wheel animations, thumbnail comparisons, before/after color corrections, hex code displays","Color wheel with tech elements, before/after thumbnails, paint splatter effect on dark background","color theory,thumbnail design,content creator tips,color psychology,youtube thumbnails,complementary colors,brand colors,thumbnail colors,click through rate,youtube ctr,color combinations,design for creators,content design,visual branding,color wheel,hex codes,thumbnail tips,youtube design,creator tools,visual content","Color theory for tech content creators — the exact color combinations that increase click-through rate by 40%.","Download our Color Palette for Creators — link in description!","TikTok, Instagram Reels, Blog Post"),
    _s("How to Write Scripts That Keep People Watching","YouTube","13:00","The first 30 seconds decide everything. Here is the formula.","1. The hook formula\n2. Open loops and curiosity gaps\n3. Pattern interrupts every 90 seconds\n4. Story structure for tech content\n5. The strong close with CTA","Average YouTube view duration is 50 percent. That means half your viewers leave before the video is half done. The fix is not better editing or flashier graphics. It is better scripting. Every video needs a hook in the first 5 seconds that makes a promise or creates curiosity. Then you open a loop. Mention something you will reveal later. This keeps people watching. Every 90 seconds you need a pattern interrupt. Change the visual. Change your tone. Show something unexpected. The human brain habituates quickly. Monotony kills retention. For tech content specifically use the problem-solution-proof structure. Show the pain. Present the fix. Prove it works.","Retention graph analysis, script structure breakdown, example hooks, before/after retention comparison","Script page with highlighted sections color-coded (hook=red, content=blue, CTA=green), retention graph","youtube scripting,video scripts,audience retention,hook formula,youtube retention,content writing,script writing,keep viewers watching,youtube tips,view duration,open loops,pattern interrupts,youtube growth,video structure,content creation,script template,youtube analytics,watch time,audience engagement,creator tips","The scripting formula that keeps viewers watching — hooks, open loops, and pattern interrupts explained.","Get our Script Template — link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post, LinkedIn"),
    _s("Building a Brand Identity for Your Tech Channel","YouTube","14:00","A logo is not a brand. Here is what actually matters.","1. Defining your brand voice\n2. Visual consistency across platforms\n3. Channel trailer and about page\n4. Intro and outro templates\n5. Building community identity","Most creators think branding means getting a logo designed on Fiverr. That is like thinking a business card is a business. Your brand is the feeling people get when they see your content. It is consistency. Every video looks like it belongs together. Same color palette. Same font style. Same energy. Your brand voice is how you talk. Are you casual or professional? Technical or accessible? Edgy or friendly? Pick a lane and commit. Our 10 channels each have distinct brand identities. Hive AI is cutting edge and bold. Hive Locksmith is practical and trustworthy. Hive Shorts is fast and punchy. Each one attracts its specific audience because the branding is intentional and consistent.","Brand board examples, channel art comparisons, style guide pages, community screenshots","Brand mood board with fonts, colors, and style elements arranged neatly, professional design feel","brand identity,tech branding,youtube branding,channel branding,brand voice,visual identity,brand consistency,content creator branding,youtube channel art,branding guide,build a brand,personal branding,creator identity,brand style guide,channel design,youtube design,brand strategy,brand personality,content branding,community building","Building a real brand identity for your tech channel — beyond logos to voice, visuals, and community.","Download our Brand Identity Workbook — link in description!","TikTok, Blog Post, LinkedIn"),
])
SCRIPT_LIBRARY["hive-shorts"].extend([
    _s("AI Answers Your Questions at 3AM","YouTube Shorts","0:45","It is 3 AM. Someone calls your business. Who answers?","Quick demo of AI answering a call","It is 3 in the morning. Your phone rings. A customer needs emergency service. Nobody is awake. Nobody answers. That customer calls the next business in Google. Sale lost. But what if AI answered? Our system picks up in one ring. Identifies the service needed. Quotes a price. Books the appointment. Sends a confirmation text. All while you sleep. The customer gets help. You get paid. Zero employees needed. This is not the future. This is running right now.","Phone ringing in dark room, AI interface activating, appointment booking animation","Dark room with phone glowing, AI brain icon answering, 3:00 AM clock display","ai phone,3am calls,ai answering,24/7 business,ai agent,automated calls,business automation,after hours,ai receptionist,night calls,emergency service,ai booking,phone bot,auto answer,business phone,ai customer service,never miss call,ai assistant,smart phone system,overnight business","What happens when a customer calls at 3AM — AI answers, books, and confirms while you sleep.","Want AI answering your calls? Link in bio!","TikTok, Instagram Reels"),
    _s("This AI Writes Better Emails Than You","YouTube Shorts","0:40","Your emails take 20 minutes. AI does it in 2 seconds.","Quick demo of AI email generation","How long do you spend writing emails every day? 30 minutes? An hour? Our AI writes professional emails in 2 seconds flat. Give it a bullet point. Hi John, following up on the lock change quote, available Thursday morning. The AI turns that into a perfect professional email with greeting, context, call to action, and signature. It matches your brand voice because it is trained on your previous emails. Not generic. Not robotic. It sounds like you but better. We process 200 emails a day this way. Same quality. A hundredth of the time.","Split screen: typing slowly vs AI generating instantly, email comparison","Email icon transforming with AI sparkles, clock showing 2 seconds, professional email preview","ai email,email automation,ai writing,fast email,professional email,email assistant,ai email writer,business email,email productivity,ai tools,email hack,quick email,email template,ai communication,email efficiency,smart email,automated email,email marketing,email tips,business productivity","AI writes professional emails in 2 seconds that sound exactly like you — trained on your writing style.","Try our AI email tool — link in bio!","TikTok, Instagram Reels"),
    _s("One Server. 30 AI Services. Zero Cloud Bills.","YouTube Shorts","0:50","We run 30 AI services on one machine. Monthly cloud cost: zero.","Quick tour of services running locally","People think you need AWS or Google Cloud to run AI. Wrong. We run 30 services on a single machine in a closet. Trading bot. Phone agent. Content engine. Chat widget. Lead generator. CRM. Dispatch system. Email server. All running 24/7. Monthly cloud bill zero dollars. The machine cost 800 dollars total. A used desktop with a graphics card. It has been running for months without downtime. Self-healing watchdog restarts any service that crashes. The trick is not expensive hardware. It is efficient code. Each service uses under 100 megabytes of RAM. Systemd manages everything. This is how startups should build.","Server room tour, htop showing processes, service dashboard, cost comparison graphic","Single server tower glowing with 30 service icons orbiting it, zero dollar bill crossed out","self hosted,no cloud,home server,30 services,zero cloud cost,server setup,local ai,self hosted ai,home lab,cheap infrastructure,server closet,systemd services,efficient code,startup infrastructure,cloud alternative,own your stack,server tour,infrastructure hack,budget tech,diy cloud","30 AI services running on one machine with zero monthly cloud costs — full home server tour.","Follow for more home lab content!","TikTok, Instagram Reels"),
    _s("Your Password Is Probably in a Database Right Now","YouTube Shorts","0:55","I will prove it. Go check haveibeenpwned.com right now.","Quick security awareness demo","Go to haveibeenpwned.com and type your email. I will wait. See that list? Those are data breaches where your password was exposed. If you use the same password on multiple sites you are already compromised. Fix it in 3 steps. Step one get a password manager. Bitwarden is free and open source. Step two generate unique passwords for every site. 20 characters minimum. Step three enable two-factor authentication everywhere. Use an authenticator app not SMS. These three steps make you harder to hack than 99 percent of people. It takes 30 minutes to set up. Do it today. Not tomorrow. Today.","haveibeenpwned.com demo, password manager setup, 2FA enrollment","Email field with red breach warnings, lock icon transforming from broken to secure, urgent red theme","password security,haveibeenpwned,data breach,password manager,bitwarden,two factor auth,2fa,online security,cyber security,password tips,security hack,protect accounts,password breach,identity theft,security awareness,password strength,authenticator app,online safety,digital security,password fix","Your password has probably been breached. Here are 3 steps to fix your security in 30 minutes.","Check your email at haveibeenpwned.com right now!","TikTok, Instagram Reels"),
    _s("How to Spot a Fake AI Product","YouTube Shorts","0:50","90 percent of AI products are just ChatGPT with a wrapper. Here is how to tell.","Quick guide to identifying AI wrappers","Someone is selling you an AI tool for 50 dollars a month. But is it actually AI or just a ChatGPT wrapper? Three red flags. One. The responses sound exactly like ChatGPT. Test by asking it to roleplay or break character. If it does it is a wrapper. Two. They cannot explain what model they use. Real AI companies know their tech stack. Three. The response time is exactly the same as ChatGPT. Real custom models have different latency characteristics. If all three flags are red you are paying 50 dollars for something you could do with a 20 dollar ChatGPT subscription. Or better yet build your own with open-source models for free.","Side-by-side comparison of wrapper vs real AI, red flag demonstrations","Magnifying glass over an AI product revealing ChatGPT logo underneath, detective theme","fake ai,ai wrapper,chatgpt wrapper,ai scam,ai products,spot fake ai,ai review,ai tools,real vs fake ai,ai fraud,chatgpt reseller,ai marketing,ai hype,ai red flags,ai buying guide,ai consumer,ai product review,overpriced ai,ai truth,ai skeptic","3 red flags that reveal an AI product is just a ChatGPT wrapper — stop paying for repackaged APIs.","Follow for honest AI reviews!","TikTok, Instagram Reels"),
])


